  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add the<strong> eggs</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for exactly 5 min, then fill a bowl of<strong> very cold water</strong> and add the <strong>cooked eggs</strong> to the bowl to cool down quickly</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681826975436-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681826975436-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681826975436-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681826975436-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681826975436-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the eggs are cooking, cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Peel and grate (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop <strong>half</strong> the <strong>red</strong> <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>remaining onion</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>to a large bowl with the <strong>rice vinegar </strong>and a pinch of<strong>  sugar</strong>, then set aside for later – these are your <strong>quick-pickled onions</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1681826980334-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1681826980334-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1681826980334-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1681826980334-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1681826980334-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p><p>Add the <strong>vegan burger patties</strong> to a large bowl with the <strong>chopped red onion</strong>, <strong>grated garlic</strong> and <strong>curry powder</strong> and give everything a good mix up (use clean hands!) – this is your <strong>veggie mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1681826985545-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1681826985545-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1681826985545-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1681826985545-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1681826985545-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a sheet of <strong>baking paper</strong> to your chopping board and sprinkle over a  generous dusting of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Form <strong>half </strong>the <strong>veggie mixture</strong> into a giant meatball, then flatten the meatball into a circle (big enough to coat an egg) onto the floured baking paper</p><p>Repeat this with the <strong>remaining veggie mixture</strong> until you have 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> <strong>veggie mixture circles</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1681826992910-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1681826992910-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
